    title: 'Reason Must Rule', theme: 'sovereignty, daily governance',
    season: 'inner_order', archetype: 'sovereign',
    invocation: 'Today you walk as the Sovereign: a man who legislates the day in the calm of morning and merely enforces it by night.',
    archetypeExpression:
      "The Sovereign governs today because daily governance is integrated command — reason ruling not by force but by structure laid down when the man is whole. He does not argue with appetite at 11 PM; he follows the law he passed at 7 AM. Today's command — letting reason legislate the morning and enforce by evening — is constitutional government of the self.",
    lineagePassageId: 'aurelius-7-29-present',
    openingLine: 'Reason does not rule by force. It rules by repetition.',
    teachingBody:
      "Reason cannot bully appetite into submission. That fight is a draw at best, and appetite often wins it. What reason can do is govern by structure, by daily practice, by the small accumulated weight of decisions made in calm moments that bind the wild moments.\n\nThis is why morning rituals matter. The morning is reason's hour. Appetite is quieter, spirit is rested, the day has not yet pulled the man in fifteen directions. The decisions made then — what the day will look like, where the phone will be at 10 PM, what the first hour after work will hold — are reason's legislation. By evening, when appetite is loud, the structure is already in place.\n\nThe Sovereign rules in the morning and is honored in the evening. Reverse that order and the kingdom falls.",
