    openingLine: 'Govern the small domains. The large ones follow.',
    teachingBody:
      "Four domains repay daily attention more than any others: speech, room, body, and time. They are the substrate of every other discipline. A man cannot meaningfully practice retention while his speech is loose, his room is chaos, his body untrained, and his time uncommanded — because the practice depends on all four.\n\nSpeech: do not speak carelessly. Do not complain reflexively. Do not gossip. Do not lie casually. Each careless sentence is a small abdication of command.\n\nRoom: keep the immediate environment ordered. Not perfect. Ordered. The space you sleep in, the space you work in, the path between them.\n\nBody: train it, feed it well, rest it on time. The body is the vehicle of every other practice.\n\nTime: know what each hour is for. Defend the hours that matter. Do not let other people's urgencies write your day.\n\nThese four, attended to daily, build the man who can hold the rest.",
