    id: 'day-52', dayNumber: 52, arcNumber: 6, arcTitle: 'The Forge',
    title: 'Energy Seeking Form', theme: 'desire as creative force, Daoist jing',
    season: 'transmutation', archetype: 'builder',
    invocation: 'Today you walk as the Builder: a man who gives desire a destination by having the vessels ready before the fire rises.',
    archetypeExpression:
      "The Builder governs today because desire is a request for form, and he is the one who keeps worthy forms waiting — the project, the training plan, the real work. Without a prepared channel, the fire returns to its cheap default, not from weakness but from architecture. Today's command — preparing the vessel before the fire rises — is the Builder converting energy into something that lasts.",
    lineagePassageId: 'synthesis-forge-the-fire',
    openingLine: 'Raw desire does not ask to be suppressed. It asks to be shaped.',
    teachingBody:
      "Desire is a request for form. The compulsion offers only one form — discharge — and the form is cheap. It returns nothing. The practice offers many forms: the trained body, the finished work, the studied page, the cleaned room, the served brother, the act of prayer. Each is a vessel that can hold the energy and return something more than what was poured in.\n\nThe Builder's craft is to have vessels ready. The man with no project, no training plan, no real work, no service relationship — when the fire rises, he has nowhere to put it. The fire returns to its default outlet. Not because he is weak, but because the architecture of his life has not been arranged for transmutation.\n\nBuild vessels. Have projects waiting. Make the worthy outlets more convenient than the unworthy ones. The fire follows the prepared channel.",
    secretContentType: 'ancient_key', secretTitle: 'Ancient Key',
    secretBody: "The medieval guild traditions understood the master craftsman as a man who had transmuted enough raw force into form that the form began to express the man. His work was recognizable; it had his fingerprints; it was him made visible. The same principle applies to the practice. The Forge is not a side activity. It is where the man becomes visible — to himself, first, and then to others. The work bears the marks of the conservation.",
    crownFragment: 'Desire is the question. Form is the answer.',
