      "Energy is not noble or ignoble in itself. It is what it enters. The same fire that becomes a finished work, a strong training session, a real conversation, or a moment of genuine attention can also become irritability, restless scrolling, the compulsion's discharge, or a fight with someone who did not deserve it. The variable is the vessel.\n\nA man who has done forty-nine days of conservation and has not built vessels will find the conserved fire running through the easiest available cracks. Conservation alone is not the discipline. Conservation plus chosen vessels is the discipline.\n\nThe Guardian's role here is to keep watch on the vessels: are they ready? are they being used? is there a project, a training, a service, a study that is genuinely receiving today's fire? If not, the fire will find something. The man chooses what.",
